    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
  "hasVerificationActivity": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-convergence-study-noncannulated",
    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Convergence Study — Non-cannulated 7.5 mm Pedicle Screw FEA Model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model using three successive global mesh densities (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~210k elements, fine: ~520k elements). Von Mises stress at the screw-rod interface and axial stiffness QoI were monitored across refinement levels. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). Results demonstrated that the medium mesh achieved GCI < 1.2% for both QoIs, satisfying the pre-defined convergence criterion. The fine mesh was used as the production mesh for all subsequent validation comparisons. Study was executed in Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 under controlled solver settings documented in the verification plan VP-001.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
    "performedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/depuy-synthes-computational-lab",
    "startedAtTime": "2023-06-01T08:00:00Z",
    "endedAtTime": "2023-06-15T17:00:00Z"
  },
